schema.name: contactProcessingThreshold
schema.title: Contact Processing Threshold
schema.description:
The constraint solver can discard solving contacts, if the distance is above this threshold. 0 by default. 
 Note that using contacts with positive distance can improve stability. It increases, however, the chance of colliding with degerate contacts, such as "interior" triangle edges

frustumCulling.title: Frustum Culling
frustumCulling.description: Controls the culling of instances against the camera frustum (frustum culling needs to enabled on each camera component). If false all instances will be rendered regardless of their visibility. Changing this setting requires application reload.

cloneMaterials.title: Clone Materials
cloneMaterials.description: If selected all instances will use a clone of the original model material. This is useful when the original material is being used in non instanced models and otherwise it will produce render artifacts. Changing this setting requires application reload.

autoDynamicCells.title: Auto Dynamic Cells
autoDynamicCells.description: If this is selected the instancer will attempt to automatically understand if an instance has moved in a cell and update it accordingly. It can have a performance hit with too many cells/instances

disableCells.title: Disable Cells
disableCells.description: Disable cells generation and do per instance culling globally. In editor this setting is being bypassed for entities to allow for individual editing.

disableShadows.title: Disable Shadows
disableShadows.description: If selected no shadows buffers will be created (optimization). Requires app reload.

bypassTransparent.title: Bypass Transparent
bypassTransparent.description: If selected transparent mesh instances will not be instanced.

excludeTag.title: Exclude Tag
excludeTag.description: Use this tag on entities to exclude them from instancing.

excludeCellsTag.title: Exclude Cells Tag
excludeCellsTag.description: Use this tag to exclude entities from being included in the global cells, if used.

shadowsOnlyTag.title: Shadows Only Tag
shadowsOnlyTag.description: Use this tag on entities to exclude them from model rendering. Those models will only render shadows.

forceTransparentTag.title: Force Transparent Tag
forceTransparentTag.description: Use this tag on entities with transparent materials to force them to be included when the Bypass Transparent flag is used.

entityDisableTag.title: Entity Disable Tag
entityDisableTag.description: Use this tag on entities to exclude them from rendering their model. It will be rendered only for shadows.

materialShadowsDisable.title: Material Shadows Disable
materialShadowsDisable.description: Use this tag on material assets to exclude them from rendering shadows.

materialCloneDisable.title: Material Clone Disable
materialCloneDisable.description: Use this tag on material assets to exclude them from cloning their material.

materialCloneEnable.title: Material Clone Enabled
materialCloneEnable.description: Use this tag on material assets to force them cloning their material.

materialNonVisible.title: Material Non Visible
materialNonVisible.description: Use this tag on material assets to force all instances to be hidden from rendering but still take part in instancing. Useful when using proxy objects to receive visibility updates.

excludeLayers.title: Exclude Layers
excludeLayers.description: Mesh instances rendered in these layers won't be instanced.

excludeShadowsLayers.title: Exclude Shadows Layers
excludeShadowsLayers.description: Payloads in these layers will skip generating shadow casters.

lodMultiplier.title: LOD Multiplier
lodMultiplier.description: The LOD multiplier all LOD Levels start/end distances will be multiplied with. Useful when creating LOD presets.

schema.name: index
schema.description: The LOD index for this level e.g. 0 for LOD0, 1 for LOD1.

schema.name: cellSize
schema.title: Cell Size
schema.description: The size of the cell in the frustum culling grid. Only static instances support cell based culling. Minimum cell side size is 1.

schema.name: updateFrequency
schema.title: Update Frequency
schema.description: Set how often in seconds culling updates will execute for this cell. To disable this check and execute it per frame set it to 0.

schema.name: updateShadowsFrequency
schema.title: Update Shadows Frequency
schema.description: Set how often in seconds culling shadows updates will execute for this cell. To disable this check and execute it per frame set it to 0.

schema.name: isDynamic
schema.title: Is Dynamic
schema.description: If selected all entities in each cell will update their world transform matrix. Useful for animating instances while in a cell. Note if an instanced changes its position to be outside its initial cell, it will not change cell automatically.

materialExtraData.title: Material Extra Data
materialExtraData.description: Materials to override their transformVS chunk to support extra instanced data.

cellSize.title: Cell Size
cellSize.description: The size of the cell in the frustum culling grid. Only static instances support cell based culling. Minimum cell side size is 1.

updateFrequency.title: Update Frequency
updateFrequency.description: Set how often in seconds culling updates will execute for this cell. To disable this check and execute it per frame set it to 0.

updateShadowsFrequency.title: Update Shadows Frequency
updateShadowsFrequency.description: Set how often in seconds culling shadows updates will execute for this cell. To disable this check and execute it per frame set it to 0.

isDynamic.title: Is Dynamic
isDynamic.description: If selected all entities in each cell will update their world transform matrix. Useful for animating instances while in a cell. Note if an instanced changes its position to be outside its initial cell, it will not change cell automatically.

schema.name: index
schema.description: The LOD index for this level e.g. 0 for LOD0, 1 for LOD1.

schema.name: layer
schema.description: Add an optional layer name to specify a LOD level for this layer only. If left blank it will be used for any layer.

schema.name: layerType
schema.description: Set what type of payloads this LOD level will apply to. If left blank it will be used for any type.

schema.name: start
schema.description: Starting from this distance from the camera this level of detail will be visible.

schema.name: end
schema.description: After this distance from the camera this level of detail will be hidden. Use 0 to keep it enabled infinitely.

proxyMesh.title: Proxy Mesh
proxyMesh.description: If an entity is referenced, as soon as its model level of detail is visible, this entity model will be hidden. Useful for hierarchical LODs. The referenced entity needs to have an instanced model rendered.

skipShadowsLod.title: Skip Shadows LOD
skipShadowsLod.description: If selected all shadowcaster instances will skip any LOD check. Useful for rendering shadows for a lower level of detail, to lower polycount. You can control which LOD casts shadows by using the model/render component Cast Shadows property.

skipShadowsOffset.title: Skip Shadows Offset
skipShadowsOffset.description: If Skip Shadows LOD is selected you can define an offset on the Y axis to adjust the rendering position of the LOD shadowcaster. Useful for removing self shadowing artifacts when rendering shadows on a level of detail with a different polycount.

resolution.title: Resolution
resolution.description: Resolution of one side of a cubemap. Use power of 2 resolution if you wish to use Mipmaps.

mipmaps.title: Mipmaps
mipmaps.description: If set to true, mipmaps will be allocated and autogenerated.

depth.title: Depth
depth.description: If set to true, depth buffer will be created.

activeCameras.title: Active Cameras
activeCameras.description: A list of cameras that render the water model, used to enable depth access to these cameras.

infiniteSurface.title: Infinite Surface
infiniteSurface.description: If selected the water surface will follow the active camera to give the illusion of an infinite water surface. Useful for sea and ocean effects.

waterScale.title: Water Scale
waterScale.description: The scale of the water surface (texture tiling).

depthOpacity.title: Depth Opacity
depthOpacity.description: Sets the amount of opacity the water will have as it gets deeper.

refractionOpacity.title: Refraction Opacity
refractionOpacity.description: Sets the amount of opacity the refraction effect will have as it gets deeper.

causticsMapAsset.title: Caustics Map
causticsMapAsset.description: The caustics map used to simulate the water caustics effects.

causticsOpacity.title: Caustics Opacity
causticsOpacity.description: Sets the amount of caustics effects the water will have as it gets deeper.

causticsIntensity.title: Caustics Intensity
causticsIntensity.description: Sets the intensity of the caustics effect.

causticsTiling.title: Caustics Tiling
causticsTiling.description: Sets the tiling of the caustics effect.

shoreOpacity.title: Shore Opacity
shoreOpacity.description: Sets the amount of shore effects the water will have as it gets deeper.

shoreIntensity.title: Shore Intensity
shoreIntensity.description: Sets the intensity of the shore effect.

shoreTiling.title: Shore Tiling
shoreTiling.description: Sets the tiling of the shore effect.

shoreFrequency.title: Shore Frequency
shoreFrequency.description: Sets the animation speed of shore effects on the water.

flowMapAsset.title: Flow Map
flowMapAsset.description: The flow map used to simulate the water flow effects.

flowFrequency.title: Flow Frequency
flowFrequency.description: Sets the animation speed of flow effects on the water.

reflectionsIntensity.title: Reflections Intensity
reflectionsIntensity.description: Sets the intensity of the reflections map.

refractionIntensity.title: Refraction Intensity
refractionIntensity.description: Sets the intensity of the refraction map.

reflectionsBumpiness.title: Reflections Bumpiness
reflectionsBumpiness.description: Sets the intensity of the reflections bumpiness.

refractionBumpiness.title: Refraction Bumpiness
refractionBumpiness.description: Sets the intensity of the refraction bumpiness.

specularColor.title: Specular Color
specularColor.description: Sets the color of the specular highlights.

specularIntensity.title: Specular Intensity
specularIntensity.description: Sets the intensity of the specular highlights.

specularBlinking.title: Specular Blinking
specularBlinking.description: If a value > 0 is provided the specular highlights will blink based on that frequency.

underwaterFogDensity.title: Underwater Fog Density
underwaterFogDensity.description: Sets the intensity of the scene fog when the active camera is under the water surface. Set to 0.0 to disable this check.

vertexWaves.title: Vertex Waves
vertexWaves.description: If selected the vertices of the water surface will animate to simulate waves. Requires a water plane with enough triangles per unit. Requires application reload.

wavesFrequency.title: Waves Frequency
wavesFrequency.description: The frequency of the sin/cos of the vertex waves.

wavesAmplitude.title: Waves Amplitude
wavesAmplitude.description: The amplitude of the sin/cos of the vertex waves.

wavesDepthMinMax.title: Waves Depth Min Max
wavesDepthMinMax.description: The min/max values to clamp the minimum and maximum wave height based on the water depth.

renderSurface.title: Render Surface
renderSurface.description: If a uranusEffectsRenderSurface entity is referenced the material will use the depth from the surface to improve the look of several effects.

mixTextureA.title: Mix Texture A
mixTextureA.description: The texture to mix from based on the alpha value provided.

mixTextureB.title: Mix Texture B
mixTextureB.description: The texture to mix to based on the alpha value provided.

mixAlpha.title: Mix Alpha
mixAlpha.description: The alpha value used to mix the base and mix textures.

animateEvent.title: Animate Event
animateEvent.description: An app wide animation event that can be called with a true/false argument and animate the transition.

animateTime.title: Animate Time
animateTime.description: The time it takes to animate a full transition when the animate event is called.

resolution.title: Resolution
resolution.description: This defines how much the resolution will be downscaled or upscaled in relation to the viewport resolution. Leverage the browser bilinear filtering to increase performance by rendering your application in a lower resolution. Or render to a higher resolution for reducing anti alias.

eventEntity.title: Event Holder
eventEntity.description: If an event entity is provided then all events will fire on that entity. Otherwise they will fire on the app object.

onRender.title: On Render
onRender.description: If an event name is provided the shader will update automatically when the event will fire. Useful when combining multiple effects on the same shader (e.g. terrain splatmaps with surface noise).

schema.name: timeOffset
schema.title: Time Offset
schema.description: You can set an optional time offset per channel to further randomize the wind animation.

schema.name: textureCoord
schema.title: Texture Coord
schema.description: Set which set of coordinates will be used to calculate the wind animation.

schema.name: textureCoordAxis
schema.title: Texture Coord Axis
schema.description: The axis on which the wind animation will play on. To use multiple axis you can add more channels.

schema.name: windBase
schema.title: Wind Base
schema.description: Set the starting coordinates value in the range of 0.0 to 1.0 for the wind animation.

schema.name: invertCoords
schema.title: Invert Coordinates
schema.description: If selected the coordinates used will be inverted.

useLocalClock.title: Use Local Clock
useLocalClock.description: Spawn a local clock instead of using the global wind timer.

windTimeSpeed.title: Wind Time Speed
windTimeSpeed.description: Can be used to control the wind animation speed, works only with a local wind clock.

windGustSize.title: Wind Gust Size
windGustSize.description: The size in world units of each  wind gust.

windDirection.title: Wind Direction
windDirection.description: The wind direction in the X and Z axis.

interactObject.title: Interact Object
interactObject.description: If selected the vertices of the model will be pushed away by any objects nearby.

interactList.title: Interact List
interactList.description: A list of entities that can interact with this material (on WebGL1 devices a maximum of 20 entities is supported).

interactRadius.title: Interact Radius
interactRadius.description: The area around each interaction entity that will be pushed away.

interactAxis.title: Interact Axis
interactAxis.description: Set the axis the vertext interact effect will be applied.

billboard.title: Billboard
billboard.description: If selected the model will be rendered as a billboard to always face the camera.

billboardLockY.title: Billboard Lock Y
billboardLockY.description: If set to true the billboard rotation will be only on Y axis, otherwise it will face the camera in all direction.

billboardReverseSize.title: Billboard Reverse Size
billboardReverseSize.description: If selected the billboard half extents calculation from the reference render asset will be reversed.

billboardRefSize.description: Provide a list of render assets for each material (in the same order), to be used for sizing the billboard.

autoSelectPreset.title: Auto Select Preset
autoSelectPreset.description: If selected a graphics preset will automatically be selected based on the device platform.

lobbyEntity.title: Lobby Entity
lobbyEntity.description: If an entity is provided the lobby entity will be enabled as soon as the settings dialog is enabled.

startEntity.title: Start Entity
startEntity.description: If an entity is provided a start button will be created to enable that entity on user's action. The lobby entity will be disabled at the same time.

playerControllers.title: Player Controllers
playerControllers.description: One or more player controllers to be used with the Toggle Controller button.

defaultController.title: Default Controller
defaultController.description: The default controller the game will start with.

grassObjects.title: Grass Objects
grassObjects.description: A list of entities to be disabled if grass is disabled in settings.

terrainEntities.title: Terrain Entities
terrainEntities.description: If one or more terrain entities are provided, they will be binded to the terrain shadows toggle.

minTerrainLod.title: Min Terrain Lod
minTerrainLod.description: The minimum terrain LOD when no shadows are cast from the terain.

schema.name: minPreset
schema.title: Min Preset
schema.description: Preset to fall back to if minimum FPS threshold is crossed. Leave blank to disable the check.

schema.name: minFps
schema.title: Min FPS
schema.description: The minimum FPS limit.

schema.name: minTime
schema.title: Min Time
schema.description: The time in seconds the FPS should be lower than the limit to force a downgrade.

schema.name: startTime
schema.title: Start Time
schema.description: The time in seconds counting from the application start the downgrade check should be enabled. Set to 0 to keep it always enabled.

schema.name: title
schema.title: Title
schema.description: The title of the preset shown in the dialog.

schema.name: resolution
schema.title: Resolution
schema.description: This defines how much the resolution will be downscaled or upscaled in relation to the viewport resolution. Leverage the browser bilinear filtering to increase performance by rendering your application in a lower resolution. Or render to a higher resolution for reducing anti alias.

schema.name: devicePixelRatio
schema.title: Device Pixel Ratio
schema.description: A normalized value 0-1 to indicate min/max device pixel ratio.

schema.name: fogNoise
schema.title: Fog Noise
schema.description: Requires page reload.

schema.name: grass
schema.title: Grass
schema.description: Requires page reload.

activeCameras.title: Active Cameras
activeCameras.description: A list of cameras to render reflections from.

materialAssets.description: If apply shader is selected, this material will be updated to have the reflections map referenced on its diffuse channel. If not, a shader uniform named texture_planarReflectionMap will be added to the material scope.

reflectionLayers.title: Reflection Layers
reflectionLayers.description: The scene layers names that are being used by models casting reflections.

refractionLayers.title: Refraction Layers
refractionLayers.description: The scene layers names that iare being used by models casting refraction.

renderPreset.title: Render Preset
renderPreset.description: Select if a reflection or refraction map will be rendered (or both). Restart is required.

resolutionFactor.title: Resolution Factor
resolutionFactor.description: Used to scale down the resolution size of the reflection render target and improve performance. Set to 1 to be equal in size with the screen size. Set to 4 to downscale the resolution 4x.

reflectionVector.title: Reflection Vector
reflectionVector.description: If set to non zero, then this normal will be used instead of the entity back direction.

reflectionOffset.title: Reflection Offset
reflectionOffset.description: Add a reflection plane offset to fine adjust the exact position of the plane.

reflectSkybox.title: Reflect Skybox
reflectSkybox.description: If selected the scene skybox will be added to the reflections.

updateFrequency.title: Update Frequency
updateFrequency.description: Set the frequency of the reflections rendered to skip this number of frames. If it is set to 0 it will update per frame.

schema.name: applyShader
schema.title: Apply Shader
schema.description: If apply shader is selected, the referenced material will be updated to have the reflections map on its diffuse channel and the diffuse shader chunk will be updated.

schema.name: uvChannel
schema.title: UV Channel
schema.description: When using Apply Shader set which UV channel should be used.

schema.name: shaderReflectionsIntensity
schema.title: Reflections Intensity
schema.description: Sets the intensity of the reflections map.

schema.name: shaderReflectionsIndex
schema.title: Reflections Index
schema.description: Sets the reflection index that affects the reflections viewing angle.

schema.name: shaderReflectionsNormalMap
schema.title: Normal Map
schema.description: If a normal is provided it will be used for the reflections in the overriden shader.

schema.name: shaderReflectionsNormalIntensity
schema.title: Normal Intensity
schema.description: Sets the intensity of the reflections normal map.

schema.name: shaderReflectionsNormalTiling
schema.title: Normal Tiling
schema.description: Sets the UV tiling of the reflections normal map.

schema.name: shaderReflectionsMask
schema.title: Mask
schema.description: If a mask is provided it will be used to mask the reflections.

schema.name: shaderReflectionsMaskTiling
schema.title: Mask Tiling
schema.description: Sets the UV tiling of the reflections mask.
